<HEAD>Great Lakes Get Strong Winds, Heavy Snow</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Heavy snow and strong winds buffeted states along the <LOCATION> Great </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lakes </LOCATION> today, causing whiteouts and traffic accidents as drifts up to 10 feet deep piled up. Snow fell in <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Utah </LOCATION>. The Great Lakes storm left more than a foot of snow in parts of northern <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION> on Wednesday night and drifts 6 to 10 feet deep. Snow advisories were in effect today in much of the state. In northeast <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>, blowing, drifting snow made snow removal difficult if not impossible. Blowing snow caused whiteouts and many traffic accidents in the area, which was under a winter storm warning. Snow squalls developed over western <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, and up to 6 inches of snow was forecast. A snow advisory was issued for northwest <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION>. Snow began falling Wednesday night in the northern mountains of <LOCATION> Southern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>, and rain fell along the coast. A winter storm warning was in effect for mountains from the <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bernardino </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Range </LOCATION> northward and in the <LOCATION> Owens </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION>. Snow advisories were posted for the <LOCATION> Antelope </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION>, northern foothills and valleys above 1,500 feet, the northern <LOCATION> Sierra </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> Lake </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Tahoe </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Basin </LOCATION>. Snow also fell in <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> George </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Cedar </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Utah </LOCATION>. A winter storm warning was in effect for the mountains of southern <LOCATION> Utah </LOCATION> and a winter storm watch was issued for mountains to the north tonight and Friday. Today's forecast calle