<HEAD>Shiite Moslem Amal Appear In Control Of South Lebanon</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By G.G. LaBELLE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>TYRE, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Fresh from victory over their rivals in the Iranian-backed <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION>, the militiamen of the Shiite Moslem Amal appear to control south <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>. The country's south is divided into strips: First, there is the Israeli-controlled security zone along the border, then an area patrolled by the <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Interim </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>, then the <ORGANIZATION> Amal </ORGANIZATION> zone running up to <LOCATION> Sidon </LOCATION>, 35 miles north of the Israeli border. Leaders of Amal say their control over south <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> means they can also control attacks on <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> soldiers in the security zone <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> proclaimed near its border in south <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>. But they would not strike at targets in <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>. `` No one is allowed to hold weapons or wear military clothes in south <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> except Amal,'' said <PERSON> Ali </PERSON> <PERSON> Kreiss </PERSON>, the local <ORGANIZATION> Amal </ORGANIZATION> political chief. `` Amal is responsible for the security of everyone in south <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>.'' The <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> peacekeepers, numbering 5,800, have been in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> since a 1978 Israeli invasion. <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> set up its security zone in 1985. <PERSON> Kreiss </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> Amal </ORGANIZATION>'s responsibility for security in south <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> was laid out in agreements signed over the last three months with the <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION>, or Party of God, and the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION>. Before the agreements, hundreds were killed in fighting with the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGA