<HEAD>Publicist Says Actor Improving, Eager To Get Back To Work</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Actor <PERSON> Gary </PERSON> <PERSON> Busey </PERSON> is making good progress and is eager to get to work on a film that was put on hold until he has recovered from a near-fatal motorcycle crash, his publicist said. `` Hopefully he will be able to go back to work and get back in the saddle soon,'' <PERSON> Carla </PERSON> <PERSON> Schalman </PERSON> said Wednesday. <PERSON> Busey </PERSON>, 44, underwent brain surgery after the Dec. 4 crash in <LOCATION> Culver </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>. He was thrown from the bike and struck his head against a curb. He was not wearing a helmet and has actively campaigned against proposals to make helmets for motorcycle riders mandatory. Ms. <PERSON> Schalman </PERSON> said an independent feature film, `` Howling at the Moon,'' was put on hold when <PERSON> Busey </PERSON> was injured. The movie describes the last day in the life of frontier lawyer <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Wesley </PERSON> <PERSON> Harding </PERSON>. <PERSON> Busey </PERSON> was cast to play the lead, Ms. <PERSON> Schalman </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Busey </PERSON>, who was initially treated at <ORGANIZATION> Cedars-Sinai </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION>, was transferred to a private facility for rehabilitation therapy. The name of the facility has been withheld to afford <PERSON> Busey </PERSON> some privacy, Ms. <PERSON> Schalman </PERSON> said. She said the actor was deluged with cards, letters and gifts shortly after the crash, but she was unsure if he had responded to them. `` The main focus has been on physical therapy, getting better and back in the swing,'' she said. `` He's making really good progress. He seems excited about that progress. He's been talking on the phone and taking exercises.'' Ms. <PERSON> Schalman </PERSON> said she did n't know when he would be released. She said she had not talked to <PERSON> Busey </PERSON> to see if he had changed his mind about the helmet law. `` The helmet law has n't come up yet. His concern, his doctors' main concern and everyone's main concern has been getting him back well and recovered.'' <PERSON> Busey </PERSON> gained fame after performing the title role in the 1978 movie, `` The Buddy Holly Story.'' His other film credits include `` Lethal Weapon,'' `` A Star is Born,'' `` Carny'' and `` The Bear.''
