<HEAD>Friends, Relatives Call Crew Members Dedicated, Enthusiastic</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Azores Crash, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The pilot and first officer of the <ORGANIZATION> Boeing </ORGANIZATION> 707 that crashed in the <LOCATION> Azores </LOCATION>, killing all 144 people on board, were described by friends and family Thursday as enthusiastic, dedicated aviators. `` He just loved motion,'' said <PERSON> Craig </PERSON> <PERSON> Abington </PERSON>, a pilot and major with the <ORGANIZATION> Tennessee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> who had known pilot <PERSON> Leon </PERSON> <PERSON> Daugherty </PERSON> since 1975. `` Most of his efforts were invested in the flying business. He really loved it,'' he said. In all, seven crew members, all American, and 137 Italian tourists died when an <ORGANIZATION> Independent </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> charter jet slammed into a mountain Wednesday in the <LOCATION> Azores </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Islands </LOCATION>. The plane, en route from <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION> to the <LOCATION> Dominican </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Republic </LOCATION>, was approaching landing for a refueling stop. <PERSON> Daugherty </PERSON>, 41, of <LOCATION> Nashville </LOCATION>, was engaged to one of the four flight attendants who died, 26-year-old <PERSON> Yvette </PERSON> <PERSON> Murray </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Marietta </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ga. </LOCATION>. Also killed were first officer <PERSON> Sam </PERSON> <PERSON> Adcock </PERSON>, 36, of <LOCATION> Nashville </LOCATION>; flight engineer <PERSON> Jorge </PERSON> <PERSON> Gonzalez </PERSON>, 34, of <PERSON> Rex </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Ga. </LOCATION>; and flight attendants <PERSON> Sabrina </PERSON> <PERSON> Cromarty </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION>; <PERSON> Helen </PERSON> <PERSON> Ziegler </PERSON>, 56, of <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Robins </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Ga. </LOCATION>; and <PERSON> Angela </PERSON> <PERSON> Urb