 provided evidence that <PERSON> Kikumura </PERSON> spent some time at a terrorist training camp in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Bekka </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION> Two days after his arrival in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Kikumura </PERSON> was sent by a roommate service to the <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION> apartment of <PERSON> Chris </PERSON> <PERSON> Brande </PERSON>. `` He was quiet and polite,'' <PERSON> Brande </PERSON>, an accountant, told the <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION>. `` Looking back now I can see a few strange things, like he said he was a tourist but I never saw a camera. `` He did n't look like a terrorist type, whatever that type is. He just seemed like a nice guy.'' <PERSON> Kikumura </PERSON> bought a used <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> 626 at <ORGANIZATION> Central </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION> in the <LOCATION> Bronx </LOCATION> within a week of his arrival in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, and he set out on his tour. On March 16, he was in <LOCATION> Gloucester </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mass </LOCATION>. He traveled west on March 22 on Interstate 80 through <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION> and stayed overnight at the <ORGANIZATION> Williams </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> bed and breakfast in <LOCATION> Avon </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lake </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>. The next night he stayed at Barnicks Bed and Breakfast in <LOCATION> Diamondsdale </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mich </LOCATION>. The Harrison Hotel in <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> was his home the night of March 24. Two days later, he was in <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Twain </PERSON>'s hometown of Hannibal, <LOCATION> Mo </LOCATION>. He also stayed March 28 in the Biltmore Hotel in <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, <LOCAT