could presumably cause greater damage in the event of a crash, he said. The hospital's bid for certification `` has very little to do with helicopters,'' said <PERSON> Horner </PERSON>. `` It has a whole lot to do with the societal obligation of Children's, which transcends Lincoln Park. It's a societal obligation that an institution of this ilk must fulfill.'' Children's cardiology service treats about 4,000 young people a year, about 10 percent of whom require heart surgery of some sort, making the hospital one of the largest of its kind in the country, <PERSON> Horner </PERSON> said. The board of the planning authority is to act on Children's application for certification at its March 2 meeting, said authority executive secretary <PERSON> Ray </PERSON> <PERSON> Passeri </PERSON>
