<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The brother of takeover strategist <PERSON> Asher </PERSON> <PERSON> Edelman </PERSON> and another businessman were indicted for an alleged multibillion-dollar phony tax shelter scheme that netted $ 511 million in improper tax writeoffs for unwitting investors. <PERSON> Asher </PERSON> <PERSON> Edelman </PERSON> was not charged with any wrongdoing or implicated at all in the alleged scheme charged Wednesday against his brother, <PERSON> Jon </PERSON>. The two defendants, <PERSON> Bernhard </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Manko </PERSON>, 48, of <LOCATION> Lighthouse </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Point </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, and <PERSON> Jon </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Edelman </PERSON>, 43, of Rye, <LOCATION> N.Y. </LOCATION>, were accused of creating more than $ 38 billion in `` pre-arranged, rigged and fraudulent'' transactions in government securities to generate tax losses for investors in numerous limited partnerships.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>BOKSBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 For 60 years, <ORGANIZATION> Colgate-Palmolive </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>'s toothpastes have helped whiten South Africans' teeth. Now, the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> company wants to break ties with a town that has become a symbol of white racism. A cordial corporate relationship with <LOCATION> Boksburg </LOCATION>, site of <ORGANIZATION> Colgate </ORGANIZATION>'s large manufacturing complex, soured in November after newly elected right-wing town councilors decided to resegegrate parks and other public facilities <ORGANIZATION> Colgate </ORGANIZATION> joined other businesses in protesting the action, and has requested its property be incorporated into the neighboring town of <LOCATION> Benoni </LOCATION> so it no longer will pay taxes to <LOCATION> Boksburg </LOCATION>.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> has proposed new rules that would crack down on stockbrokers who use high-pressure telephone tactics to sell penny stocks. The stocks can be thinly traded and it is often difficult for an investor to accurately judge their value. Brokers sometimes take extra-large commissions on penny stock sales. The <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> rule, proposed Wednesday, would not entirely ban unsolicited `` cold calls.'' However, it would require brokerage firms to sign a written agreement with a new customer before completing a transaction.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Fancier foods, individual video machines and money-back guarantees are among the amenities that big airlines are offering to first-class fliers as competition for travelers increasingly highlights service instead of price. The latest campaign was unveiled Wednesday by <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION>, which said it is investing $ 40 million to upgrade its first-class service on long-haul flights beginning March 1. The changes, detailed at a news conference in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, include individual passenger video terminals at each seat, redesigned cabin interiors, a new wine cellar and menus that allow passengers to eat when they wish.
